0lawsuit%20by%20government%20employee%20unions%20against%20USAID%20cuts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUSAID%20spent%20%2432.5%20billion%20in%202024%20on%20global%20humanitarian%20aid.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20has%20partially%20blocked%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-usaid-ukraine-middle-east-foreign-aid-aids-vaccinations-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattempt%20to%20dismantle%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Carl%20Nichols%20said%20in%20a%20Friday%20order%20he%20would%20temporarily%20block%20the%20Trump%20administration%20from%20placing%202%2C200%20USAID%20employees%20on%20paid%20leave%20until%20midnight%20on%20February%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20USAID%20personnel%20work%20in%20'high-risk%20environments%20where%20access%20to%20security%20resources%20is%20critical.'%20No%20future%20lawsuit%20could%20undo%20the%20physical%20harm%20that%20might%20result%20if%20USAID%20employees%20are%20not%20informed%20of%20imminent%20security%20threats%20occurring%20in%20the%20countries%20to%20which%20they%20have%20relocated%20in%20the%20course%20of%20their%20service%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20Nichols%20wrote%20in%20his%20order%2C%20preventing%20the%20layoffs%20from%20taking%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20argued%20at%20the%20TRO%20hearing%20that%20placing%20employees%20on%20paid%20administrative%20leave%20is%20a%20garden-variety%20personnel%20action%20unworthy%20of%20court%20intervention.%20But%20administrative%20leave%20in%20Syria%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20administrative%20leave%20in%20Bethesda%3A%20simply%20being%20paid%20cannot%20change%20that%20fact%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge's%20order%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge's%20order%20partially%20grants%20a%20temporary%20restraining%20order%20requested%20by%20two%20labor%20groups%20representing%20federal%20workers%20in